OL,3,CFormer trampoline park owner spared
OL,4,Cjail for food hygiene violations
OL,6,FA former trampoline park owner has
OL,7,Fbeen spared jail for food hygiene
OL,8,Fviolations while serving a suspended
OL,9,Fsentence for breaching safety laws.
OL,11,FPhilip Booth, 68, received a 12month
OL,12,Fprison sentence, suspended for 10
OL,13,Fmonths, in June 2023 after showing a
OL,14,F"total disregard" for health and
OL,15,Fsafety legislation when a number of
OL,16,Fchildren broke limbs at Supajump in
OL,17,FCardiff.
