OL,3,CFormer trampoline park owner spared
OL,4,Cjail for food hygiene violations
OL,6,FCardiff Crown Court heard that
OL,7,FSupertramp Ltd, trading as Supajump,
OL,8,Fwas voluntarily placed into
OL,9,Fliquidation by Booth in July 2025.
OL,11,FIn mitigation, Booth's legal
OL,12,Frepresentative said he is currently
OL,13,Funemployed, receiving Universal
OL,14,FCredit, and living at his parents'
OL,15,Fhome, where he acts as a carer for
OL,16,Fboth, who have dementia. The court
OL,17,Fheard he earns #600 a month, including
OL,18,Fhis carer's allowance, and that his
OL,19,Fcompany was formally liquidated in
OL,20,FJuly 2025.
